rComments: Probably one of the best professors i've ever had. I highly recommend it to students who are in their first year deciding whether to continue with studio major. She will definitely change the way you have been approaching art.
She is not very open to new ideas. If it is not her way then it must be wrong

She is absolutely horrendous. She has favorites and makes it abundantly clear that the other students in the class cannot even come close to winning her favor. She grades based on her personal judgements of the person, and ignores any sort of creativity if it is not what she decides as being "art".
listening to her comments is like listening to your death sentence
Not a very good profesor.  She is very narrow minded, and has her favourites in the class.  I do not recomend anybody to take her classes, studio major or not.

Tanya is a prof you want to have at UTSC.  She may seem a bit intimidating- but she's fair. Tells you how it's done and she's honest (don't be surprised if she tells you ur work is crap- bc she has a reason to). Can't wait to have her in my class.
A lil intimidating but still good.
